{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"99286abd-c352-4c8e-9b91-64291e44e70b","content":"\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, VSTest switches map to native flags passed after `--`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/*[Category=Integration]\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --collect-coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--treenode-filter \"/*[Category=Integration]\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Notes:**\n- Everything after `--` bypasses VSTest and goes directly to the new runner.\n- The tree-node filter property name (e.g. `Category`) must match your framework's trait name exactly (`TestCategory` for MSTest, `Category` for NUnit).\n- You'll need the **Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport**, **Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage**, and **Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump**/**HangDump** NuGet packages referenced in your test project.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4a241b53-2b68-42c5-87d1-a39be7e7a49b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling, not a codebase task.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform (the new test runner), the CLI changes significantly:\n\n1. `dotnet test` still works but the arguments change\n2. `--filter` becomes `--filter` (same, but uses `--treenode-filter` for the new platform's native filter syntax)\n3. `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n4. `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage, or you configure it differently\n\n\n5. Blame-related arguments like `--blame-crash` and `--blame-hang` map to `--crashdump` and `--hangdump`, with timeout arguments following the same pattern\n6. When using `dotnet test` with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, arguments after `--` get passed through to the test runner, and filtering can use either the legacy `--filter` syntax or the new `--treenode-filter` format for more granular control\n\nNow I'm clarifying the exact command syntax and how various logging and diagnostic options translate in this newer testing framework. I'm realizing the property name in the tree node filter depends on the test framework—MSTest uses `TestCategory`, NUnit uses `Category`, and xUnit uses traits differently. Since the user specified `Category=Integration`, I'll keep that but note they may need to adjust based on their framework.","outputTokens":1344},"id":"26aa85be-0195-4b4e-ac23-293beee4ec87","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:46:28.685Z","parentId":"7e52f4cb-2cee-455b-8019-99df13210485"}
